---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | Ochre & Chrome" description="Privacy policy for Ochre & Chrome.">
  <main class="editorial-page legal-page legal-page--structured">
    <SiteHeader />

    <section class="legal-hero">
      <p class="oc-kicker">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>
        This policy explains how personal data is processed when you visit Ochre & Chrome.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Pascal Misoph<br />
        Holbeinstr. 7<br />
        01307 Dresden<br />
        Germany<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:hello@ochreandchrome.com">hello@ochreandchrome.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>General Website Access</h2>
      <p>
        When you visit this website, technical access data may be processed automatically by the
        hosting provider. This can include IP address, date and time of access, requested URL,
        referrer URL, browser type, operating system, transferred data volume, and server status
        messages.
      </p>
      <p>
        The purpose is to deliver the website, maintain security, prevent misuse, and troubleshoot
        technical issues. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR. The legitimate interest is reliable,
        secure, and efficient operation of this website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted by Vercel Inc., 440 N Barranca Ave #4133, Covina, CA 91723, USA.
        Vercel may process technical access data to provide hosting, content delivery, security,
        and deployment services.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data may be processed in the United States. Where data is transferred internationally, the
        transfer is based on appropriate safeguards such as standard contractual clauses or other
        mechanisms available under GDPR.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Fonts</h2>
      <p>
        This website loads fonts from Google Fonts. When the fonts are loaded, your browser may
        connect to Google servers and transmit technical information such as your IP address and
        browser data. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR. The legitimate interest is consistent,
        performant visual presentation of the website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        The website uses essential local storage to remember your cookie preference. This storage is
        necessary so the banner does not appear on every page view and so your choice can be changed
        later through the footer link.
      </p>
      <p>
        Optional analytics and marketing categories are only activated if you choose them in the
        cookie banner. At this stage, no separate analytics or marketing tools are loaded by the
        website.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can change your choice at any time by using the Cookie Settings link in the footer or by
        deleting site data in your browser.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Contact by Email</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact us by email, we process the personal data you provide, such as your email
        address, name, message content, and any metadata transmitted with the message. The purpose is
        to respond to your request. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR where the communication is
        related to pre-contractual or contractual matters, and Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR for general
        inquiries.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Affiliate Links and External Websites</h2>
      <p>
        Product references may link to external websites. When you follow an external link, the
        privacy policies of the respective external provider apply. Affiliate links are not active
        until verified partner destinations are added.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Technical server data is retained only as long as necessary for delivery, security,
        troubleshooting, and legal obligations. Email inquiries are retained as long as needed to
        respond and to document the communication where legitimate interests or legal obligations
        require it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You have the right to request access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, data
        portability, and to object to processing where the legal requirements are met. Where
        processing is based on consent, you may withdraw consent at any time with effect for the
        future.
      </p>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. In Saxony, the
        competent authority is the Sächsische Datenschutz- und Transparenzbeauftragte.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>No Automated Decision-Making</h2>
      <p>
        This website does not use automated decision-making or profiling within the meaning of Art.
        22 GDPR.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Updates</h2>
      <p>
        This privacy policy may be updated when website features, providers, analytics, newsletter
        tools, shop functions, or affiliate integrations change.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
